derivation.yuyuan_name: late Middle English: via Old French from Latin inaestimabilis, from in- 'not' + aestimabilis (see estimable)

entry.tran: 难以计算的;无法估计的
entry.def: If you describe the value, benefit, or importance of something as inestimable, you mean that it is extremely great and cannot be calculated.

example.ex: Human life is of inestimable value...
This gives the professional an inestimable advantage.
example.tran: 这给了专业人士一个无法估量的优势。
